1) Product / Task Definition

Product Name:
FreightPOP Accessorial Recommendation Agent

AI Capability Type:

☐ Conversational Assistant
☐ RAG Q&A
☐ Content Generation
☐ Structured Extraction
☑ Agent / Workflow
☐ Other

Core Task:
During LTL shipment creation, automatically detect missing accessorial charges
(Liftgate / Residential Delivery / Limited Access) based on address, weight,
package type, and unload equipment availability — preventing unexpected carrier
surcharges after delivery.

Target Users:
Operations staff at freight brokers and shippers who create LTL shipments in a TMS.

High-Value Scenarios:

1. Residential + Heavy Freight: Most common source of missed accessorials;
   liftgate + residential delivery combined surcharges are highest
2. Restricted Locations (schools, hospitals, construction sites, government buildings,
   airports, malls, etc.): Operators often unaware these trigger Limited Access fees
3. Ambiguous Address + Unknown Unload Equipment: Operator unsure about destination;
   system should surface advisory before shipment is booked

High-Risk Errors:

☑ Hallucination (recommending accessorial types that don't exist)
☑ False Negatives (missing a required accessorial → post-delivery surcharge dispute)
☑ False Positives (recommending unnecessary accessorial → increased customer cost)
☑ High Latency (blocking the shipment creation workflow)
☑ Cost Overrun (AI invoked unnecessarily on clear-cut cases)

