8) Error Analysis & Iteration

v1 Issues (resolved in v2):

1. False Positive on A4 Rule (TC-003): residential + 3 handling units triggered
   limited_access at confidence 0.60. This was a gray-area rule that caused operator
   confusion and incorrect charges.
   Root cause: Rule A4 was too aggressive for this signal combination.
   Fix: A4 removed in v2. Residential + multiple handling units now generates an
   advisory (delivery_complexity) instead of a recommendation.

2. AI Confidence Boundary Violation (AI-001 v1): AI pushed liftgate confidence to 0.85,
   violating the < 0.85 constraint.
   Root cause: LLM imprecision on boundary arithmetic (0.84 vs 0.85).
   Fix: Code-level guardrail in analyzer.js caps confidence at 0.84 before output.
   No user-facing impact.

3. AI Test Case Design Error (AI-005 v1): High-confidence residential + liftgate case
   was expected to skip AI, but multi-recommendation cases always trigger Task 1.
   Root cause: Test expectation was wrong, not the rules.
   Fix: AI-005 redesigned in v2 — uses dock=yes + forklift=yes to suppress liftgate,
   leaving only residential_delivery(0.95) which skips AI correctly.

Known Open Issue (v2):

Dead code in liftgate scoring (newrules.js line 180):
   `else if (effectivePkg === 'loose' && weight >= 300)` never fires because
   `weight >= 150` on the preceding line always catches it first.
   Impact: The +0.20 "very heavy loose freight" bonus is unreachable.
   Current behavior: loose freight ≥ 150 lbs always gets +0.15 (not +0.20).
   Severity: Low — liftgate still fires for these shipments, bonus is just smaller.
   Action: Fix the else-if to if in a follow-up iteration.

